This significantly increases the time required to crack the password.&nbsp; &nbsp;</li><li>Hash Generation: The result of the key stretching process is used to generate a fixed-length hash.</li><li>A typical Bcrypt hash looks like this:$2a$10$vI1UF0Nt3JAuhVo0O2QzpuF6j3LUdAu9u01L9qLJ6519rHt00j4u.<br></li></ol><p></p>" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;overflow=hidden;rounded=0;" vertex="1" parent="1"> <mxGeometry x="38.5" y="1120" width="460" height="190" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="wTH0yocXQ4WSepD2pJDL-58" value="<h1 style="margin-top: 0px;">How PBKDF2 works</h1><p></p><ol><li>Salting: A unique salt is generated for each password.
